From affd956caec89e1b86f8d66da66bc8a90553916d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 15:07:31 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Signal-scheduler bridge: store-claimed pinned lanes +
 pass/commit/mutation reports

An external signal store owns update scheduling: it claims a transition lane
per store batch (claimTransitionLane) and pins it on the transition objects it
dispatches under (transition._signalLane, honored by requestTransitionLane),
so corrective re-renders land inside the owning batch's commit. React reports
pass starts (prepareFreshStack), per-root commits, and the exact DOM mutation
window (flushMutationEffects bracket) through one bridge object published at
globalThis.__SIGNALS_ROYALE_FX1__.
---
